        public QualificationBuilder loadFromJsonString(String json)
        Create the qual object from a simple JSON string. Sample JSON: 
             {
         "ID": [10, 11, 12],
         "MaidenName": "Alice",
         "$or": [ { "FirstName": "Bob" }, { "$and" : [ { "LastName": "Smith" }, { "MaidenName": { "$neq": "Smith" } } ] } ]
         "DateOfBirth": { "$gt": "01/01/2001", "<": "01/01/2010" }
         "$restricting": {
             "Address": {
                 "Description": { "<>": "" }
             }
         }
     }

      • fromEntityKeys

        public QualificationBuilder fromEntityKeys(EntityInstance source,
                                           boolean linkEntities)
        Use the keys from 'source' to qualify the entity.
        Parameters:
        source -
        linkEntities - if true and the target entity is the root then the entities will be relinked after the activate. This is used to activate a list with rootonly-multiple and then activating one of the roots. The root will be be current if the OI is updated.
        Returns:
